To have the answers a master nameserver for a domain vary
depending on who is asking the question?

The example that prompted this question is a site may want to
vary the order of the MX records it returns depending on whether
the questioner is local or distant.  If it's a distant questioner
I may want to tell them something like

	IN	MX	0 &lt;given-host&gt;
	IN	MX	1 s.ms.uky.edu
	IN	MX	2 e.ms.uky.edu
	IN	MX	3 g.ms.uky.edu
	IN	MX	4 ncc.uky.edu
	IN	MX	5 b.ee.engr.uky.edu
	IN	MX	100 uunet.uu.net

But for one on the local net I may want to either not return an MX
record or return one *only* listing the given host, or a list like
above but headed by the given host and not containing the questioning host.

-- 
&lt;- David Herron; an MMDF guy                              &lt;david@ms.uky.edu&gt;
&lt;- ska: David le casse\*'      {rutgers,uunet}!ukma!david, david@UKMA.BITNET
&lt;- 
&lt;- The problem with mnemonics is they mean different things to different people.

